Title: The entropy of near-extreme N=2 black holes
Authors: Klaus Behrndt, Mirjam Cvetic and Wafic A. Sabra
Comments: Latex, 13 pages
Report-no: HUB-EP-97/93
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D58 (1998) 084018
\\
  We give an explicit form of the classical entropy for four-dimensional static
near-BPS-saturated black holes of generic N=2 superstring vacua. The expression
is obtained by determining the leading corrections in the non-extremality
parameter to the corresponding BPS-saturated black hole solutions. These
classical results are quantitatively compared with the microscopic leading
order corrections to the microscopic result of Maldacena Strominger and Witten
for N=2 BPS-saturated black holes.
